OL,6,FIn a statement, her daughter Gemma
OL,7,Fsaid her mother was a "kind, loving
OL,8,Fand friendly person whose smile lit up
OL,9,Fa room. She enjoyed going to church,
OL,10,Fcooking and gardening and loved family
OL,11,Ftrips to Mablethorpe to "smell the sea
OL,12,Fair".
OL,14,FElaine Turbill died in 2017. Her
OL,15,Fdaughter said seven years on, the pain
OL,16,Fnever goes away.
OL,18,FShe said she feels her mother's death
OL,19,Fcould have been prevented, which would
OL,20,Fhave given her the opportunity to see
OL,21,Fher second grandchild.
